&gt;
&gt;     In the Read Alphabet, how do you, personally, write the second
&gt;     syllable of the word February? Do you use letters 2-25-40, or
&gt;     2-17-40? I pronounce it the way it is spelled. This makes me a
&gt;     little peculiar, since most people say what they hear other people
&gt;     say without regard to the spelling.
&gt;     Vin
&gt;     On 9/2/2012 10:19 PM, Ryan wrote:
&gt;&gt;     Hi everyone. I&#39;ve just joined and am excited to find there are
&gt;&gt;     other people in the world interested in the Read Alphabet.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     I first heard of Quikscript back in the late 90&#39;s and early
&gt;&gt;     2000&#39;s, and at the time I thought I was just about the only
&gt;&gt;     person interested. Just today someone mentioned Shaw and it got
&gt;&gt;     me thinking about Shavian and Quikscript, so I did a quick search
&gt;&gt;     and found this group.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     Back when I first heard about the alphabet I got pretty far in
&gt;&gt;     teaching myself to read and write, though I think I eventually
